From: Assistant <assistant@example.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add UAPI header for vo_mipi_tx

The middleware requires a userspace-compatible vo_mipi_tx.h header,
but only a kernel-internal version exists in interdrv/vo/chip/. This
patch creates a proper UAPI header that can be used by userspace
applications without requiring kernel-internal headers.

Signed-off-by: Assistant <assistant@example.com>
---
 interdrv/include/chip/cv181x/uapi/linux/vo_mipi_tx.h | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 interdrv/include/chip/cv181x/uapi/linux/vo_mipi_tx.h

diff --git a/interdrv/include/chip/cv181x/uapi/linux/vo_mipi_tx.h b/interdrv/include/chip/cv181x/uapi/linux/vo_mipi_tx.h
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1a1e5b5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/interdrv/include/chip/cv181x/uapi/linux/vo_mipi_tx.h
@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@
+#ifndef _UAPI_VO_MIPI_TX_H_
+#define _UAPI_VO_MIPI_TX_H_
+
+/* UAPI header for MIPI TX interface */
+#include "cvi_comm_mipi_tx.h"
+
+int mipi_tx_get_combo_dev_cfg(struct combo_dev_cfg_s *dev_cfg);
+
+#endif /* _UAPI_VO_MIPI_TX_H_ */
